to remedy this situation are welcome).
Aside from the fact that I was so tired I could barely function, I did
survive. Saw hoosiers for $1950-$2200. Saw some nifty gold metal letters ( 2
feet high, maybe) that spelled out &quot;Roses 25 cents&quot; (can't find the cent key on
this keyboard). I think, cool (!) and ask how much? $1800. I pretend like
this is not a shock (ha!) and walk away. Saw some nifty advertising signs for
grape cola for $40. I even bought one. Saw them later at another booth for
$145. Yes, he bought them that morning. I asked. Revolving piano stools are
still only $95.
Anyway...filled up the van in about 8 hours and turned around and came
home. Whew! Anyone else go? Love to hear your impressions. Fayette

