I have to say I was disappointed in this Brimfield. I have been to the
May brimfield shows this being my third year.

1. It was way way more crowded. Various cable home shows and Martha
Stewart have certainly helped increase attendance. Which I will admit is
great for the dealers.

2. Because of the crowds the prices were much higher than previous
brimfields. In fact, in March I was in France at a few flea markets there
and with the exception of the incredibly priced Paris flea markets the
prices and deals were way better.

3. I was disappointed to see so many dealers at Brimfield dabbling in
selling Beanie Babies

I do like the no setting up early rule contrary to previous posts. This
was enacted by several fields years ago to prevent dealer to dealer
selling prior to the start. In fact, last year several dealers were
thrown out for selling before the field opened.

P Davis

